headline: One-Off Gain Drives Profit Margin Higher at Equity Residential (EQR), Raising Quality Concerns
summary: Equity Residential (EQR) delivered a profit margin of 37.5%, increasing from 31.5% a year ago, as earnings grew 24.8% year over year. This growth far outpaces its 5-year average of just 0.7% per year. While revenue is projected to rise at 4.2% per year, which lags the broader US market's expected 10.2% annual growth, analysts see earnings declining at a pace of -17.9% per year over the next three years. summary: Equity Residential's fair value estimate was recently lowered slightly, moving from $73.80 to $73.35 per share following new analysis that reflects updated outlooks.
